post.description: Uploads a photo. Uploading apps can call the flickr.people.getUploadStatus method in the regular API to obtain file and bandwidth limits for the user.

parameters.name: title
parameters.description: The title of the photo. Optional.

parameters.name: description
parameters.description: A description of the photo. May contain some limited HTML. Optional.

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: A space-seperated list of tags to apply to the photo. Optional.

parameters.name: is_public
parameters.description: Set to 0 for no, 1 for yes. Specifies who can view the photo. Optional.

parameters.name: is_friend
parameters.description: Set to 0 for no, 1 for yes. Specifies who can view the photo. Optional.

parameters.name: is_family
parameters.description: Set to 0 for no, 1 for yes. Specifies who can view the photo. Optional.

parameters.name: safety_level
parameters.description: Set to 1 for Safe, 2 for Moderate, or 3 for Restricted. Optional.

parameters.name: content_type
parameters.description: Set to 1 for Photo, 2 for Screenshot, or 3 for Other. Optional.

parameters.name: hidden
parameters.description: Set to 1 to keep the photo in global search results, 2 to hide from public searches. Optional.

parameters.name: async
parameters.description: Flickr can process photos in async mode, for applications that need to post multiple photos and don't want to wait around for each one to complete, leaving a socket connection open the whole time. Set to 1 for async mode, 0 for sync mode.

parameters.description: The ID of the account to fetch the collection tree for. Deafults to the calling user.

parameters.description: A space-seperated list of tags to apply to the photo. Optional.

parameters.name: tag_mode
parameters.description: Either 'any' for an OR combination of tags, or 'all' for an AND combination. Defaults to 'any' if not specified.

parameters.name: text
parameters.description: The text to search for.

parameters.name: min_upload_date
parameters.description: Minimum upload date. Photos with an upload date greater than or equal to this value will be returned. The date should be in the form of a unix timestamp.

parameters.name: max_upload_date
parameters.description: Maximum upload date. Photos with an upload date less than or equal to this value will be returned. The date should be in the form of a unix timestamp.

parameters.name: min_taken_date
parameters.description: Minimum taken date. Photos with an taken date greater than or equal to this value will be returned. The date should be in the form of a mysql datetime.

parameters.name: max_taken_date
parameters.description: Maximum taken date. Photos with an taken date less than or equal to this value will be returned. The date should be in the form of a mysql datetime.

parameters.name: license
parameters.description: The license id for photos (for possible values see the flickr.photos.licenses.getInfo method). Multiple licenses may be comma-separated.

parameters.name: sort
parameters.description: The order in which to sort returned photos. Deafults to date-posted-desc (unless you are doing a radial geo query, in which case the default sorting is by ascending distance from the point specified). The possible values are: date-posted-asc, date-posted-desc, date-taken-asc, date-taken-desc, interestingness-desc, interestingness-asc, and relevance.

parameters.name: privacy_filter
parameters.description: Return photos only matching a certain privacy level. This only applies when making an authenticated call to view photos you own. Valid values are: 1 (public photos), 2 (private photos visible to friends), 3 (private photos visible to family), 4 (private photos visible to friends and family), 5 (completely private photos)

parameters.name: hbox
parameters.description: A comma-delimited list of 4 values defining the Bounding Box of the area that will be searched. See API docs for more info.

parameters.name: accuracy
parameters.description: Recorded accuracy level of the location information. Current range is 1-16: World level is 1, Country is ~3, Region is ~6, City is ~11, Street is ~16. Defaults to maximum value if not specified.

parameters.name: safe_search
parameters.description: Safe search setting. Accepted values: 1 (safe), 2 (moderate), 3 (restricted)

parameters.name: content_type
parameters.description: Set to 1 for Photo, 2 for Screenshot, or 3 for Other. Optional.

parameters.name: machine_tags
parameters.description: Machine tag(s). See API docs for format. Multiple machine tags may be queried by passing a comma-separated list. The number of machine tags you can pass in a single query depends on the tag mode (AND or OR) that you are querying with. "AND" queries are limited to (16) machine tags. "OR" queries are limited to (8).

parameters.name: machine_tag_mode
parameters.description: Either 'any' for an OR combination of tags, or 'all' for an AND combination. Defaults to 'any' if not specified.

parameters.name: group_id
parameters.description: The NSID of the group to fetch information for.

parameters.name: contacts

parameters.name: place_id
parameters.description: A Flickr place id. (not used if bbox argument is present). See API docs for more info.

parameters.name: media

parameters.name: geo_context

parameters.name: lon
parameters.description: A valid longitude, in decimal format, for doing radial geo queries. See API docs for more info.

title.description: The title of the photo. Optional.

description.description: A description of the photo. May contain some limited HTML. Optional.

tags.description: A space-seperated list of tags to apply to the photo. Optional.

is_public.description: Set to 0 for no, 1 for yes. Specifies who can view the photo. Optional.

is_friend.description: Set to 0 for no, 1 for yes. Specifies who can view the photo. Optional.

is_family.description: Set to 0 for no, 1 for yes. Specifies who can view the photo. Optional.

safety_level.description: Set to 1 for Safe, 2 for Moderate, or 3 for Restricted. Optional.

content_type.description: Set to 1 for Photo, 2 for Screenshot, or 3 for Other. Optional.

hidden.description: Set to 1 to keep the photo in global search results, 2 to hide from public searches. Optional.

async.description: Flickr can process photos in async mode, for applications that need to post multiple photos and don't want to wait around for each one to complete, leaving a socket connection open the whole time. Set to 1 for async mode, 0 for sync mode.

photo_id.description: The ID of the photo to replace.

format.description: Response format. Accepted values: rest (REST), xmlrpc (XML-RPC), soap (SOAP), soap2 (Alternate SOAP) json (JSON), php_serial (Serialized PHP).

per_page.description: Number of items to return per page. If this argument is omitted, it defaults to 10. The maximum allowed value is 50.

page.description: The page of results to return. If this argument is omitted, it defaults to 1.

timeframe.description: The timeframe in which to return updates for. This can be specified in days ('2d') or hours ('4h'). The default behavoir is to return changes since the beginning of the previous user session.

mini_token.description: The mini-token typed in by a user. It should be 9 digits long. It may optionally contain dashes.

service.description: Optionally only return blogs for a given service id. You can get a list of from flickr.blogs.getServices().

blog_id.description: The ID of the blog to post to.

blog_password.description: The password for the blog (used when the blog does not have a stored password).

collection_id.description: The ID of the collection to fetch information for.

user_id.description: The ID of the account to fetch the collection tree for. Deafults to the calling user.

filter.description: An optional filter of the results. The following values are valid: friends (Only contacts who are friends, and not family), family (Only contacts who are family, and not friends), both (Only contacts who are both friends and family), neither (Only contacts who are neither friends nor family).

date_lastupload.description: Limits the resultset to contacts that have uploaded photos since this date. The date should be in the form of a Unix timestamp. The default offset is (1) hour and the maximum (24) hours.

min_fave_date.description: Minimum date that a photo was favorited on. The date should be in the form of a unix timestamp.

max_fave_date.description: Maximum date that a photo was favorited on. The date should be in the form of a unix timestamp.

extras.description: A comma-delimited list of extra information to fetch for each returned record. Currently supported fields are: description, license, date_upload, date_taken, owner_name, icon_server, original_format, last_update, geo, tags, machine_tags, o_dims, views, media, path_alias, url_sq, url_t, url_s, url_m, url_z, url_l, url_o

gallery_id.description: The ID of the gallery to add a photo to. Note: this is the compound ID returned in methods like flickr.galleries.getList, and flickr.galleries.getListForPhoto.

comment.description: A short comment or story to accompany the photo.

primary_photo_id.description: The first photo to add to your gallery.

photo_ids.description: A comma-delimited list of photo ids to include in the gallery. They will appear in the set in the order sent. This list must contain the primary photo id. This list of photos replaces the existing list.

cat_id.description: The category id to fetch a list of groups and sub-categories for. If not specified, it defaults to zero, the root of the category tree.

group_id.description: The NSID of the group to fetch information for.

lang.description: The language of the group name and description to fetch. If the language is not found, the primary language of the group will be returned. Valid values are the same as in feeds.

membertypes.description: Comma separated list of member types. Accepted values: 2 (member), 3 (moderator), 4 (admin). By default returns all types. (Returning super rare member type "1: narwhal" isn't supported by this API method)

date.description: A specific date, formatted as YYYY-MM-DD, to return interesting photos for.

predicate.description: Limit the list of namespaces returned to those that have the following predicate.

namespace.description: Limit the list of pairs returned to those that have the following namespace.

panda_name.description: The name of the panda to ask for photos from. You can fetch a list of all the current pandas using the flickr.panda.getList API method.

find_email.description: The email address of the user to find (may be primary or secondary).

username.description: The username of the user to lookup.

min_upload_date.description: Minimum upload date. Photos with an upload date greater than or equal to this value will be returned. The date should be in the form of a unix timestamp.

max_upload_date.description: Maximum upload date. Photos with an upload date less than or equal to this value will be returned. The date should be in the form of a unix timestamp.

min_taken_date.description: Minimum taken date. Photos with an taken date greater than or equal to this value will be returned. The date should be in the form of a mysql datetime.

max_taken_date.description: Maximum taken date. Photos with an taken date less than or equal to this value will be returned. The date should be in the form of a mysql datetime.

privacy_filter.description: Return photos only matching a certain privacy level. This only applies when making an authenticated call to view photos you own. Valid values are: 1 (public photos), 2 (private photos visible to friends), 3 (private photos visible to family), 4 (private photos visible to friends and family), 5 (completely private photos)

owner_id.description: An NSID of a Flickr member. This will restrict the list of photos to those taken by that member.

count.description: Number of photos to return. Defaults to 10, maximum 50. This is only used if single_photo is not passed.

just_friends.description: Set as 1 to only show photos from friends and family (excluding regular contacts).

single_photo.description: Only fetch one photo (the latest) per contact, instead of all photos in chronological order.

include_self.description: Set to 1 to include photos from the calling user.

dates.description: A comma delimited list of unix timestamps, denoting the periods to return counts for. They should be specified smallest first.

taken_dates.description: A comma delimited list of mysql datetimes, denoting the periods to return counts for. They should be specified smallest first.

secret.description: The secret for the photo. If the correct secret is passed then permissions checking is skipped. This enables the 'sharing' of individual photos by passing around the id and secret.

media.description: Filter results by media type. Possible values are all (default), photos, videos

min_date.description: A Unix timestamp or any English textual datetime description indicating the date from which modifications should be compared.

tag_id.description: The tag to remove from the photo. This parameter should contain a tag id, as returned by flickr.photos.getInfo.

tag_mode.description: Either 'any' for an OR combination of tags, or 'all' for an AND combination. Defaults to 'any' if not specified.

license.description: The license id for photos (for possible values see the flickr.photos.licenses.getInfo method). Multiple licenses may be comma-separated.

sort.description: The order in which to sort returned photos. Deafults to date-posted-desc (unless you are doing a radial geo query, in which case the default sorting is by ascending distance from the point specified). The possible values are: date-posted-asc, date-posted-desc, date-taken-asc, date-taken-desc, interestingness-desc, interestingness-asc, and relevance.

hbox.description: A comma-delimited list of 4 values defining the Bounding Box of the area that will be searched. See API docs for more info.

accuracy.description: Recorded accuracy level of the location information. Current range is 1-16: World level is 1, Country is ~3, Region is ~6, City is ~11, Street is ~16. Defaults to maximum value if not specified.

machine_tags.description: Machine tag(s). See API docs for format. Multiple machine tags may be queried by passing a comma-separated list. The number of machine tags you can pass in a single query depends on the tag mode (AND or OR) that you are querying with. "AND" queries are limited to (16) machine tags. "OR" queries are limited to (8).

machine_tag_mode.description: Either 'any' for an OR combination of tags, or 'all' for an AND combination. Defaults to 'any' if not specified.

contacts.description: Search your contacts. Either 'all' or 'ff' for just friends and family. (Experimental)

woe_id.description: A 32-bit identifier that uniquely represents spatial entities. (not used if bbox argument is present). See API docs for more info.

place_id.description: A Flickr place id. (not used if bbox argument is present). See API docs for more info.

has_geo.description: Any photo that has been geotagged, or if the value is "0" any photo that has not been geotagged. See API docs for more info.

geo_context.description: Geo context is a numeric value representing the photo's geotagginess beyond latitude and longitude. See API docs for more info. Accepted values: 0 (not defined), 1 (indoors), 2 (outdoors)

lat.description: A valid latitude, in decimal format, for doing radial geo queries. See API docs for more info.

lon.description: A valid longitude, in decimal format, for doing radial geo queries. See API docs for more info.

radius.description: A valid radius used for geo queries, greater than zero and less than 20 miles (or 32 kilometers), for use with point-based geo queries. The default value is 5 (km).

radius_units.description: The unit of measure when doing radial geo queries. Valid options are "mi" (miles) and "km" (kilometers). The default is "km".

is_commons.description: Limit the scope of the search to only photos that are part of the Flickr Commons project. Default is false.

is_gallery.description: Limit the scope of the search to only photos that are in a gallery? Default is false, search all photos.

is_getty.description: Limit the scope of the search to only photos that are for sale on Getty. Default is false.

date_posted.description: The date the photo was uploaded to flickr (see the dates documentation)

date_taken.description: The date the photo was taken (see the dates documentation)

date_taken_granularity.description: The granularity of the date the photo was taken (see the dates documentation)

perm_comment.description: Who can add comments to the photo and its notes. one of: 0: nobody, 1: friends & family, 2: contacts, 3: everybody.

perm_addmeta.description: Who can add notes and tags to the photo. one of: 0: nobody / just the owner, 1: friends & family, 2: contacts, 3: everybody.

comment_id.description: The id of the comment to edit.

min_comment_date.description: Minimum date that a comment was added. The date should be in the form of a unix timestamp.

max_comment_date.description: Maximum date that a comment was added. The date should be in the form of a unix timestamp.

date_lastcomment.description: Limits the resultset to photos that have been commented on since this date. The date should be in the form of a Unix timestamp. The default, and maximum, offset is (1) hour.

contacts_filter.description: A comma-separated list of contact NSIDs to limit the scope of the query to.

context.description: Context is a numeric value representing the photo's geotagginess beyond latitude and longitude. For example, you may wish to indicate that a photo was taken "indoors" or "outdoors". The current list of context IDs is: 0 (not defined), 1 (indoors), 2 (outdoors). The default context for geotagged photos is 0, or "not defined".

is_contact.description: 1 to set viewing permissions for the photo's location data to contacts, 0 to set it to private.

license_id.description: The license to apply, or 0 (zero) to remove the current license. Note : as of this writing the "no known copyright restrictions" license (7) is not a valid argument.

note_x.description: The left coordinate of the note

note_y.description: The top coordinate of the note

note_id.description: The id of the note to delete

person_x.description: The left-most pixel co-ordinate of the box around the person.

person_y.description: The top-most pixel co-ordinate of the box around the person.

person_w.description: The width (in pixels) of the box around the person.

person_h.description: The height (in pixels) of the box around the person.

degrees.description: The amount of degrees by which to rotate the photo (clockwise) from it's current orientation. Valid values are 90, 180 and 270.

tickets.description: A comma-delimited list of ticket ids

photoset_id.description: The id of the photoset to add a photo to.

photoset_ids.description: A comma delimited list of photoset IDs, ordered with the set to show first, first in the list. Any set IDs not given in the list will be set to appear at the end of the list, ordered by their IDs.

query.description: The query string to use for place ID lookups.

url.description: A flickr.com/places URL in the form of /country/region/city. For example: /Canada/Quebec/Montreal

place_type_id.description: The numeric ID for a specific place type to cluster photos by. Valid place type IDs are: 22 (neighborhood), 7 (locality), 8 (region), 12 (country), 29 (continent).

bbox.description: A comma-delimited list of 4 values defining the Bounding Box of the area that will be searched. The 4 values represent the bottom-left corner of the box and the top-right corner, minimum_longitude, minimum_latitude, maximum_longitude, maximum_latitude.

place_type.description: Deprecated in favor of place_type_id. The name of place type to using as the starting point to search for places in a bounding box. Valid placetypes are: neighbourhood, locality, county, region, country, continent.

threshold.description: The minimum number of photos that a place type must have to be included. If the number of photos is lowered then the parent place type for that place will be used.

method_name.description: The name of the method to fetch information for.

domain.description: The domain to return referrers for. This should be a hostname (eg: "flickr.com") with no protocol or pathname.

tag.description: The tag that this cluster belongs to.

cluster_id.description: The top three tags for the cluster, separated by dashes (just like the url).

period.description: The period for which to fetch hot tags. Valid values are day and week (defaults to day).
